# App Launch — Prioritized To-Do List


## 🟠 Pre-Launch (Core Features)

- [ ] **Account tiers** — Maintain two separate account pages (standard and premium); standard users should not see premium/production tools to avoid overwhelm as well as maintain value in the premium service
- [ ] **Location locking** — Employees can only clock in within a set radius (~100m) of the registered business address
  - Food trucks: when start-of-day report is submitted, record a location ping; all staff must check in within ~100m of that ping
  - Multiple trucks require separate licenses; no simultaneous sign-in across physically separate locations
  - Ghost kitchens operating multiple brands from one address are fine on a single license (data will not be separated by brand)
- [ ] **Workflow caching & directory** — Store all workflows created or imported by free-tier users; cache parsed results to avoid duplicate AI parse costs; build a browsable workflow directory (e.g. "Browse Directory" or "Import Workflow")
  - Enforce no blog post attachments
  - Only scrape recipe ingredients and steps (not blog content — copyright risk)
  - Parse workflows for equipment references (required vs. recommended)
- [ ] **Barcode printing (app)** — Print barcodes tied to active batches (maybe because its mid fermentation. not sure if the print QR button should have options but it should definitely import that batch and open it at the last completed step for the user that scans it.); scanning with the app shows batch details (workflow, current step, timer, claimed status) and allows claiming. Printing the barcode should release that workflow from any user that has claimed it.
- [ ] **New user tutorial** — Interactive onboarding walkthrough for first-time users

---

## 🟡 Post-Launch (Growth Features)

- [ ] **POS integration** — Connect to major POS systems (Square, Toast, Lightspeed, Clover, etc.) to pull in sales data for costing and revenue analytics; export data in appropriate formats (CSV, XLSX, etc.)
- [ ] **Web embed tool** — Paid embeddable widget for third-party websites to display workflow operations (branded "Powered by Batch Maker" or similar)
- [ ] **Language packs** — Downloadable language packs to translate the app UI; allows multilingual teams to work in their native language
- [ ] **QuickBooks integration** — Sync cost tracking and financial data
- [ ] **Google Calendar sync** — Schedule and view batches on a calendar

---

## 🔵 Future / Enterprise

- [ ] **Predictive batch scheduling** — Use POS sales and pre-order data to suggest production increases; calendar alerts for time-sensitive prep (e.g. day-before cold ferment); requires POS integration first
- [ ] **Customer order tracking**
- [ ] **Inventory management**
- [ ] **Staff scheduling**
- [ ] **Equipment maintenance logs**
- [ ] **Multi-location dashboard support**
- [ ] **Role-based permissions** — Manager, supervisor, operator levels

---

## 🐛 Current Website Bugs

- [ ] **Page wipe on action** — Performing any action on the website (cancelling/releasing a batch, marking an item as ordered, etc.) clears the entire page contents until a manual refresh. Affects every page. Must be fixed before launch — unacceptable UX.
- [ ] **Archive feature missing from website** — The app has workflow archiving; the website does not. Needs parity.
- [ ] **Team status display broken** — Team status panel is not displaying correctly. Should only show employees who are currently clocked in to that location — nothing else.